      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 17
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 is a purist\u2019s specification, featuring the naturally aspirated 3.4L flat-six mated to a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The M96 power unit delivers linear torque across the rev range, benefiting from a documented IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement. Performance is sharpened by a factory-optioned limited-slip differential and a refreshed suspension geometry featuring Bilstein dampers. Braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors, ensuring consistent thermal management. While showing minor patina consistent with its mileage, the chassis remains rigid and the throttle response is telepathic. A mechanically robust example ready for the canyon roads.",
